<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.damniwish.com/2008/12/quick-bloggin-1.html</guid>
<description>If your writing style is snarky, cynical, or devil's advocate--there's a good chance that you just sound like a bitter ass. Writing in that style is almost impossible to pull off well. That's why there are very few professional critics...</description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>If your writing style is <em>snarky</em>, <em>cynical</em>, or <em>devil's advocate</em>--there's a good chance that you just sound like a bitter ass.&nbsp; </p> <p>Writing in that style is almost impossible to pull off well. That's why there are very few professional critics out there.</p> <p>Even if readers enjoy your blog, they probably aren't going to do business with you. I may want to read someone's snippy take on business, but I sure wouldn't want to spend any time with them. I'd rather work with a nice guy.</p><div class="feedflare">
